tasks.description:
Create src/ports/mod.rs. Imports: NONE. Must define:

1. trait RandomNumberGenerator { fn gen_range(&self, min: u32, max: u32) → u32; }
2. trait UserInterface {
   fn welcome(&self);
   fn prompt_guess(&self) → u32;
   fn display_feedback(&self, msg: &str);
   fn victory(&self, secret: u32, guesses: u32);
}

NO implementations. These are boundaries only. Code must compile with zero imports.

Create src/adapters/secondary/mod.rs. Imports: ONLY crate::ports + rand. Must:

1. Import: use crate::ports::RandomNumberGenerator;
2. Import: use rand::{thread_rng, Rng};
3. Define: pub struct OsRandomGenerator;
4. impl RandomNumberGenerator for OsRandomGenerator {
   fn gen_range(&self, min: u32, max: u32) → u32 { thread_rng().gen_range(min..=max) }
}

IMPORTANT: NO other imports, NO domain layer import, NO other adapters.

Create src/adapters/primary/mod.rs. Imports: std::io + crate::ports ONLY. Must:

1. Import: use std::io::{self, Write};
2. Import: use crate::ports::UserInterface;
3. Define: pub struct StdioUI;
4. impl UserInterface for StdioUI { all 4 methods using println!/print!/io::stdin() }

IMPORTANT: NO domain import, NO other adapters, NO rand/external crates.

Create src/adapters/mod.rs with:
pub mod primary;
pub mod secondary;

This file ONLY declares submodules.

Create src/usecases/mod.rs. Imports: crate::domain + crate::ports ONLY. Must:

1. Import domain types and ports
2. Define: pub struct GameOrchestration;
3. impl GameOrchestration {
   pub fn run(rng: &dyn RandomNumberGenerator, ui: &dyn UserInterface) {
     ui.welcome();
     let secret = rng.gen_range(1, 100);
     let mut game = GameState::new(secret);
     loop {
       let guess = ui.prompt_guess();
       if guess < 1 || guess > 100 { ui.display_feedback("Invalid"); continue; }
       game.guesses += 1;
       match game.guess(guess) {
         GuessResult::TooLow => ui.display_feedback("Too low"),
         GuessResult::TooHigh => ui.display_feedback("Too high"),
         GuessResult::Correct => { ui.victory(secret, game.guesses); break; }
       }
     }
   }
}

IMPORTANT: NO adapter imports, NO external crates, ONLY domain + ports.

Create src/main.rs. This is the ONLY file allowed to import adapters. Must:

1. mod domain; mod ports; mod adapters; mod usecases;
2. use adapters::primary::StdioUI;
3. use adapters::secondary::OsRandomGenerator;
4. use usecases::GameOrchestration;
5. fn main() { GameOrchestration::run(&OsRandomGenerator, &StdioUI); }

IMPORTANT: This file ONLY wires the game together. NO business logic here.
